    <item>
      <title>Conception Illustration</title>
      <link>https://smileguide.github.io/en/docs/myoc/pedia/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 06 Jun 2023 21:23:49 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://smileguide.github.io/en/docs/myoc/pedia/</guid>
      <description>Since RSS readers do not display the blog content perfectly, please read this article in your browser.<br/>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;earthlyworld&#34;&gt;Earthly World&lt;/span&gt; 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idearthlyworldearthly-worldspan&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idearthlyworldearthly-worldspan&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The world we live in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;husoul&#34;&gt;Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idhusoulmankinds-motosoul&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idhusoulmankinds-motosoul&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Moto&lt;/em&gt; is a Japanese word that means &lt;em&gt;original&lt;/em&gt;.Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul is the original soul of a person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Sufaddition of Motosoul 
    &lt;div id=&#34;sufaddition-of-motosoul&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#sufaddition-of-motosoul&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When two Owners of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s&amp;rsquo;s True Soul are subjected to the Heavenly Torture, due to the fact that two EL Travellers cannot exist simultaneously, the pain is halved. The first to arrive will successfully become an EL Traveller, with double the spiritual energy bonus, while the other&amp;rsquo;s soul will be shattered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;leafworld&#34;&gt;Leaf World 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idleafworldleaf-world&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idleafworldleaf-world&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Parallel worlds in the fourth dimension. The World of Leaves can establish connections and communicate with the Owners of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul through mental control. Dreams are the only way to travel between Our World and the World of Leaves through the four-dimensional axis. It is said that only children can have such a &lt;em&gt;dream of the Leaf World&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;leafsoul&#34;&gt;Leaf Motosoul 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idleafsoulleaf-motosoul&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idleafsoulleaf-motosoul&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The projection of the soul of Owners of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul in the Leaf World.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;tay&#34;&gt;tai 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idtaytai&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idtaytai&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After arriving in the World of Leaves, the owner of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul loses their freedom and cannot return until they become an EL Traveller. Such a person who loses their freedom is called a tai (meaning &lt;em&gt;body&lt;/em&gt; in Japanese)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;eltraveller&#34;&gt;EL Traveller 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-ideltravellerel-traveller&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-ideltravellerel-traveller&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An Owner of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul who can travel back and forth between Our World and the Leaf World through dreams. Karlukle is an EL Traveller who gains L-abilities every night by sleepwalking in the Leaf World and lands in various corners of Earthly World to engage in conversations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;GOTENSAMA&lt;/em&gt; 
    &lt;div id=&#34;gotensama&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#gotensama&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The personification of Leaf World, which means &lt;em&gt;Heaven Lord&lt;/em&gt; in Japanese.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;gotensamastorture&#34;&gt;Heavenly Torture 
    &lt;div id=&#34;span-idgotensamastortureheavenly-torture&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#span-idgotensamastortureheavenly-torture&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The torture of Leaf World which involves both physical and mental torment. When being subjected to the Heavenly Torture, there is a slow-splitting pain  in the body and great despair in the mind. To gain freedom, one must endure the torture and become an EL Traveller.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Owner of Mankind&amp;rsquo;s Motosoul 
    &lt;div id=&#34;owner-of-mankinds-motosoul&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#owner-of-mankinds-motosoul&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Humans(those who possess souls).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Background Q&amp;A</title>
      <link>https://smileguide.github.io/en/docs/myoc/questionaire/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 06 Jun 2023 23:00:25 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://smileguide.github.io/en/docs/myoc/questionaire/</guid>
      <description>Since RSS readers do not display the blog content perfectly, please read this article in your browser.<br/>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why use the family name &amp;ldquo;Amano(天野)&amp;rdquo;? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;why-use-the-family-name-amano天野&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#why-use-the-family-name-amano%e5%a4%a9%e9%87%8e&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have been searching for a family that sounds catchy in English. The word &amp;ldquo;Ama(天)&amp;rdquo; related to the theme of this story attracted me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What is the origin of the name &amp;ldquo;Karlukle(カルクル)&amp;rdquo;? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;what-is-the-origin-of-the-name-karlukleカルクル&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-the-origin-of-the-name-karlukle%e3%82%ab%e3%83%ab%e3%82%af%e3%83%ab&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I first gave the protagonist an English name &amp;ldquo;Karlukle&amp;rdquo;.
Karlukle consists of two parts, &lt;em&gt;Karl&lt;/em&gt; is a Germanic and Scandinavian variant of &amp;ldquo;Charles&amp;rdquo;, and &lt;em&gt;Ukle&lt;/em&gt; is taken from &lt;em&gt;Ukulele&lt;/em&gt;.
At the same time, when translating Karlukle into Katakana, I learned from the name of Howl&amp;rsquo;s apprentice in Studio Ghibli&amp;rsquo;s anime film &lt;em&gt;Howl&amp;rsquo;s Moving Castle(ハウルの動く城, 2004)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What is the meaning of the name &lt;em&gt;Jin Chengmin(金丞旻)&lt;/em&gt;? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;what-is-the-meaning-of-the-name-jin-chengmin金丞旻&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-the-meaning-of-the-name-jin-chengmin%e9%87%91%e4%b8%9e%e6%97%bb&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Min(旻)&lt;/em&gt; means sky, corresponding to &lt;em&gt;Amano&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why is it the &lt;em&gt;Leaf&lt;/em&gt; World? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;why-is-it-the-leaf-world&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#why-is-it-the-leaf-world&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Parallel universe is connected by the fourth dimension, which easily reminds people of countless parallel leaves on a branch.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
      
